cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with scheduling workflows in the cloud environment, which involves distributed and parallel computing. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also likely as the paper mentions testing the algorithms on scientific workflows and workflows from an in-production cluster of an online streaming service company. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with scheduling jobs with precedence constraints and limited budget, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper deals with scheduling in the cloud environment, which involves networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper formulates the scheduling problem as an integer programming problem and proposes a prioritization scheme based on Markovian chain stationary probabilities.
